com.gh.bmd.jrt.android.builder

Interface ServiceRoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>

  • Type Parameters:
    INPUT - the input data type.
    OUTPUT - the output data type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    ConfigurableBuilder<RoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>>, Routine<INPUT,OUTPUT>, RoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>, ServiceConfigurableBuilder<ServiceRoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>>

    public interface ServiceRoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>
extends RoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>, ServiceConfigurableBuilder<ServiceRoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>>
    Interface defining a builder of routine objects based on an invocation class token.
    The invocation execution will happen in a dedicated service.

    The local context of the invocations will be the specific service instance.

    Note that, like the object passed to the service routine input and output channels, the invocation factory arguments must comply with the Parcel.writeValue(Object) method. Be aware though, that issues may arise when employing Serializable objects on the Lollipop OS version, so, it is advisable to use Parcelable objects instead.

    Created by davide-maestroni on 3/7/15.
